<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="133" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1511,1824]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1511,1536]" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A moderately elongate species with yellow face, partly yellowish pleuron, and blackish abdomen without fasciae of golden pile. Smaller (
<quantity box="[604,684,1547,1571]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="11.0">11 mm</quantity>
) and more compactly built than the similarly coloured, larger (
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="13.0">13– 14 mm</quantity>
) and more elongate 
<taxonomicName box="[460,549,1584,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Microdon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sava">
<emphasis box="[460,549,1584,1607]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="133">M. sava</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
